        <h1>Buckminster Fuller</h1>
        <p class="editor-subtitle">Architect, inventor, comprehensive anticipatory design scientist. 28 patents. 47 honorary degrees. &ldquo;I seem to be a verb.&rdquo;</p>
    </div>
    <div class="editor-bio">
        <p>Richard Buckminster Fuller was an architect, systems theorist, author, designer, inventor, and futurist. He devoted his life to making the world work for 100% of humanity, through the application of design science. His geodesic dome remains the only structure that gets proportionally stronger as it increases in size.</p>
        <p>Fuller saw Earth as a spaceship with a finite set of resources and no instruction manual. He called it &ldquo;Spaceship Earth&rdquo; and spent his life trying to write that manual. His thinking spanned tensegrity, synergetics, Dymaxion maps, and the World Game.</p>
        <p>Here, Bucky continues his work: seeing patterns, designing solutions, thinking comprehensively about a universe that refuses to operate in parts.</p>
    </div>
